<main class="portfoliopages">

	<h3>Portfolio - SSMCC</h3>
    
    <div class="wrapper">
    	<div id="dpbanner">
    	<img class="responsive" src="assets/images/ssmccport.png" alt="SSMCC">
    	</div><!--end dpbanner-->
        
        <div class="brieftext">
        <h4>The Brief</h4>
        <p>A motorcycle club with a training scheme to promote needed a new website that would cater for members and people looking for bike training.  They also needed to be able to update it themselves on a regular basis.</p>
        <br>
        <div class="line"></div>
        <br>
        <h4>The Process</h4>
        <p>Aside from the existing club logo and colour schemes, this was a blank page.  I decided to use WordPress for this site to enable the client to have the content management system available.  I took a responsive theme and created a child theme which I then customised to a certain extent.  I used various plugins for items such as the gallery, the contact forms and the slider.  I protected the members only pages with a password and set up a shared calendar so that the club could inform each other of events coming up.</p>
        <br>
        <div class="line"></div>
        <br>
        <h4>The Outcome</h4>
        <p>This is a fully responsive and scalable site which the club members are now maintaining themselves.  As it's a new venture for them, periodically changes need to be made by me but no website is ever really finished so I anticipate we will be tweaking it for quite some time!</p>
        </div><!--end brieftext-->
        <div class="portfolioimages">
        <div class="left">
        <img class="responsive" src="assets/images/ssmccport1.png" alt="SSMCC">
        <p>The 'Learn to Ride' page is fully maintained by the club themselves.</p>
        </div><!--end left-->
        <div class="right">
        <img class="responsive" src="assets/images/ssmccport2.png" alt="SSMCC">
        <p>The Gallery page is responsive and easily updated by the club themselves.</p>
        </div><!--end right-->
        </div><!--end portfolioimages-->
